> Anyway, i've seen how sveltekit developers replied in other cases when someone complained about the documentation so I will stop here with my feedback.

{irony-mode}
Yeah, that's it. Basically if you are a beginner in SvelteKit, you don't deserve SvelteKit. You must learn SvelteKit to understand the docs.
Go, learn swimming and then maybe you'll be granted to use this **free and philanthropic** tool those masters gifted us and you, miserable worm, dared to criticize.
{/irony mode}
